<p>III<br/>and were also at it practically all the time for the 2 succeeding days and nights. During this time we were shelled almost constantly by the Turks but in my Battery (the 8th) the casualties were fortunately very small. I think out of those four days we hardly slept a wink but did not seem to miss it as there was plenty to do. I am getting a rather interesting photo today I hope of the different class of missiles heaved at us, from an 8.2 inch shell down to a 3 pounder.<br/>Late on the night of the 6th, while things were still pretty willing in our quarter, a fresh force consisting of English and Indian troops was landed on our left, and these encircled the Turks on that flank and drove them towards us, and here again our field guns played havoc with them.<br/>As I said before things have</p>
